body:
there is no git repo, which download from github release,
however, acrn-dm -v will get tag info from this repo, in
such case, the tag info was null.
this patch will fix nul tag, which get it from CL mock build.

Signed-off-by: Wei Liu <weix.w.liu@intel.com>
Reviewed-by: Jason Chen CJ <jason.cj.chen@intel.com>
title: DM: add tag info while no repo in release

body:
Ensure we have a /dev/mmcblk1p3 device before we can launch
the guest OS service.

This will be help to not launch the acrn guest service on devices
which don't have MMC.

Exmaples are NUC with sata devices or installation on non APL MRB.
title: Ensure we have MMC device as in GP2.0
